  "observation": "Brainstorm triggered by plateau. 4 proposals generated.",
  "suggestion": "The plateau likely reflects organisms trapped in a 'local dead end': they evolve good enough survival to persist a few steps, then die before expressing any complex morphology. Beauty never gets scored because organisms never survive long enough. The fitness=0.0 suggests no lineages are even completing a reproductive cycle. The system needs either (a) longer organism lifespans OR (b) multiple strategy branches OR (c) environmental structure that rewards diverse solutions. Current architecture forces convergence to one survival strategy that is marginally viable. Structural change needed.; [medium] Introduce metabolic symbiosis: Add new cell types (storage, converter, symbiont) that enable organisms to form energy-sharing collectives. Single organisms remain viable but collectives unlock 2x efficiency bonus and new beauty dimensions (collective symmetry, emergent pattern formation). Organisms must choose: maximize solo survival OR cooperative survival with shared resource pools. — Plateau suggests all organisms are trapped in the same competitive strategy. Symbiosis opens a new strategy branch where cooperation becomes viable. Collective beauty (synchronized movement, geometric patterns) can't emerge in isolated organisms. This adds dimensionality without changing physics.; [hard] Replace homogeneous world with environmental gradients: Add light-source zones, temperature gradient, nutrient-density map. Organisms evolve to sense (new sensory cells) and navigate gradients. Introduce phototaxis, thermotaxis as new action types. Beauty metrics reward elegant gradient-following patterns (spirals, waves) and emergent segregation patterns. — Current flat world forces all organisms into identical niches. Gradients create spatial heterogeneity. Organisms that navigate gradients efficiently survive longer (more time to express beauty). Emergent patterns (biofilms, herding along gradients) become possible and rewarded. This is structural — world physics change, not parameter tuning.; [easy] Decouple beauty from immediate fitness; introduce aesthetic selection phase: Split each cycle into (1) survival phase (only survivalRate + efficiency matter) and (2) aesthetic phase where beauties t organisms seed the next generation at 1.5x frequency. Remove beauty from real-time fitness, make it a selection bias instead. Organisms evolve survival first, beauty emerges downstream. — Current composite fitness may be selecting for survival-optimized organisms that look 'ugly' (clumpy, rigid). Those organisms die before producing offspring, blocking beauty evolution. Decoupling creates two selection pressures that work in sequence, not competition. Allows lineages to evolve beauty AFTER achieving baseline survival.",
